caAERS CAAERS-2769 Treatment type must be optional Bug Closed Critical Fixed Ramachandra Rao Seethiraju paul.baumgartner 8/27/2009 9:48 9/3/2009 11:13 Version 1.9.5 Version 1.9.6 Module 1: Adverse Event Data Capture 4-Sep-09 0               Per Ann Setser and Shanda Finnigan Per Ann Setser and Shanda Finnigan, treatment type must be optional when creating a course.

There are two options for this implementation.
Option A:
If treatment type is not selected, no solicited AEs should be shown.
The rules should run (i.e. assume it is NOT baseline)
If the treatment type is selected later, the solicited AEs should be shown and any previously added AEs that are solicited AEs should populate the appropriate solicited AE.

Option B:
If treatment type is not selected, assume it is a non-baseline period. Don't show solicited AEs, and don't automatically merge if it is later selected.
